    {
      "id": 10,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        120,
        560
      ],
      "size": [
        440,
        260
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 10,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "sky = ON in this workflow.\nAtlasInput segments the sky with SAM3/semantic, inpaints the\nforeground occluders, and projects the clean plate onto a sky card.\n\nsky = OFF disables the entire sky card and passes the image\nstraight to the relief mesh. Pick OFF if you want MoGe depth."
      ],
      "title": "SWITCH 1 \u00b7 SKY"
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        620,
        940
      ],
      "size": [
        460,
        320
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 11,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "depth_model controls the monocular depth backend.\n\n\u2022 V2-Metric-Outdoor (default) = best all-round, works with sky ON.\n\u2022 V2-Metric-Indoor = interior twin.\n\u2022 MoGe-* = cleanest geometry, but sky=ON auto-switches you to\n  V2-Metric-Outdoor because MoGe masks sky poorly.\n  Use sky=OFF if you specifically want MoGe depth."
      ],
      "title": "SWITCH 2 \u00b7 DEPTH MODEL"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        1120,
        940
      ],
      "size": [
        520,
        280
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 12,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "layers + mesh choose the geometry strategy.\n\n\u2022 layers=0, mesh=relief \u2192 one full-range depth-following mesh.\n\u2022 layers=0, mesh=card/ground \u2192 one flat plane.\n\u2022 layers=2/3/4 \u2192 watertight depth-band clean-plate layers.\n\u2022 use_vlm=True \u2192 VLM picks per-band geometry and prompts."
      ],
      "title": "SWITCH 3 \u00b7 LAYERS / MESH"
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        1700,
        860
      ],
      "size": [
        500,
        360
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 13,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "scope_prompts = per-line SAM segmentation for each band.\ninpaint = LaMa crop/stitch clean plates for occluded bands.\n\nsky_inpaint_mode = lama (fast deterministic) or sdxl\n(generative). The sky card always gets its own inpaint.\n\nFor real foreground-geometry override, move past AtlasInput and\nuse AtlasDeriveProjectionGeometry / AtlasDeriveReliefMesh /\nAtlasCleanPlateStack / AtlasMergeGeometry, or the blockout viewport."
      ],
      "title": "SWITCH 4 \u00b7 INPAINT / SCOPE"
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        2240,
        940
      ],
      "size": [
        520,
        280
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 14,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "SWITCH 5 \u00b7 LIVE HOLE FILL\n\nOnly applies to layers=0, mesh=relief (single full-range mesh).\n\n\u2022 live_fill_holes = ON runs a ZBrush-style Close Holes pass on the\n  relief mesh before it is stored in the solve.\n\u2022 live_fill_distance_m caps the forward depth of the fill so\n  distant voids (sky, far backdrop) stay open.\n\u2022 live_fill_max_hole_edges skips large boundary loops that are\n  probably real disocclusions better handled by clean plates.\n\nFor full manual control use AtlasDeriveReliefMesh or\nAtlasDeriveProjectionGeometry directly."
      ],
      "title": "SWITCH 5 \u00b7 LIVE HOLE FILL"
    }
  ],
